## Where someone lives makes a difference.

Research shows that pills are available by mail in all states, even in states that ban clinic-based abortion care. Using pills by mail is {% inlineLink action={discriminant: "internal", value: {page: "protocol"}} _language="" %}medically safe{% /inlineLink %}.

Using pills by mail may come with some legal risk for those who live in a state that has restrictions on abortion (like a total ban or gestation restrictions).

To understand the legal risks, contact the ReproLegal Helpline, a free legal resource that can help answer questions: visit {% inlineLink action={discriminant: "external", value: {url: "https://www.reprolegalhelpline.org", showPopup: false}} _language="" %}reprolegalhelpline.org{% /inlineLink %} or call or text 844-868-2812.
{% /bodySection %}

