## Have legal questions?

Once someone decides to have an abortion, they should be able to do so safely, effectively, and with dignity. No one should be arrested or jailed for ending their own pregnancy.

If someone gets into trouble for having an abortion, it is important for them to get legal help. Organizations that offer legal help are:

- {% inlineLink action={discriminant: "external", value: {url: "https://www.reprolegalhelpline.org/sma-contact-the-helpline", showPopup: false}} _language="" %}Repro Legal Helpline{% /inlineLink %} provides free, confidential legal support {% inlineLink action={discriminant: "external", value: {url: "https://www.reprolegalhelpline.org/sma-contact-the-helpline", showPopup: false}} _language="" %}online{% /inlineLink %} or at [844-868-2812](tel:8448682812). They also defend people who are prosecuted or threatened with prosecution for self-managing their abortion. This {% inlineLink action={discriminant: "external", value: {url: "https://www.reprolegalhelpline.org/sma-contact-the-helpline", showPopup: false}} _language="" %}fact sheet{% /inlineLink %} also has some great information about legal issues.
- {% inlineLink action={discriminant: "external", value: {url: "https://www.nationaladvocatesforpregnantwomen.org/issues/abortion", showPopup: false}} _language="" %}Pregnancy Justice{% /inlineLink %} defends women who are pregnant and attempt to have abortion, actually have an abortion, or are mistaken as someone who has had an abortion.
